members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.size
members.description: Returns the number of key/value pars in the status map.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.entries()
members.description: Returns a new Iterator object containing an array of [key, value] for each element in the status map, in insertion order.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.forEach(callback[, argument])
members.description: Calls callback once for each key-value pair in the status map, in insertion order. If argument is present it will be passed to the callback.

parameters.name: callback
parameters.description: Function to execute for each element, taking three arguments: currentValue The current element being processed in the array. index The index of the current element being processed in the array. array Which array forEach() is being applied to.

parameters.name: currentValue
parameters.description: The current element being processed in the array.

parameters.name: index
parameters.description: The index of the current element being processed in the array.

parameters.name: array
parameters.description: Which array forEach() is being applied to.

parameters.name: thisArg Optional
parameters.description: Value used as this when executing callback.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.get()
members.description: Returns the value associated with the given key, or undefined if there is none.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key whose value you want returned.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.has()
members.description: Returns a boolean asserting whether a value has been associated with the given key.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key whose value you want returned

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.keys()
members.description: Returns a new Iterator object containing keys for each element in the status map, in insertion order.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.values()
members.description: Returns a new Iterator object containing values for each element in the status map, in insertion order.

members.name: MediaKeyStatusMap.[@@iterator]()
members.description: Returns a new Iterator object containing an array of [key, value] for each element in the status map, in insertion order.
